### Describe the bug

This issue is about Blazor WASM standalone (no server)
When publishing a new version with no nuget packages updated, only actual code, of a Blazor WASM app, sometimes errors occurs when loading the app. For ex: `MONO_WASM: TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'out')`

The app stops at the loading screen.

We are hosting it in Azure Container Apps as a docker container behind nginx with this config:
```events { }
http {
    include mime.types;

    server {
        listen 8080 default_server;
        server_name _;

        add_header blazor-environment ${ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT};

        add_header Cache-Control "no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate";
        
        location / {
            root      /usr/share/nginx/html;
            try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html =404;
        }
    }
}
```


### Expected Behavior

The app should load latest resources etc.

### Steps To Reproduce

1. Let a Blazor WASM app run for some weeks
2. Update source code and deploy a new version
3. Errors occurs while loading the app

### Exceptions (if any)

`MONO_WASM: TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'out')`

### .NET Version

8.0.100

### Anything else?

We have tried clearing cache programatically, the "dotnet-resources-/" cache specifically - does not work
We have tried set `Cache-Control: "no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate"` - does not work
We have tried set `<BlazorCacheBootResources>false</BlazorCacheBootResources>` - does not work
We have tried set `<script src="_framework/blazor.webassembly.js?v=some random number"></script>` - does not work 

If the end user does CTRL+SHIFT+R it works. This seem to be the only solution but its not acceptable.

We have debugged a user who experienced the issue using Dev Tools, we could see that blazor.webassembly.js was not stale and it loaded all the .wasm files.

The users reporting this seem to all use Microsoft Edge (this might not be entirely true, but this is what has been reported and observed).

